Premier David Makhura says the province will pursue criminal charges. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Soweto has the highest number of active COVID-19 cases in Gauteng. Premier David Makhura says resources will be directed to the area to ensure regulations are followed. "There is a slowdown with regards to the surge and I want to continue to say that observing that is comforting, but we cannot send out a message that we are out of the woods," he said. READ: Makhura: SIU identified officials at centre of alleged PPE corruption Makhura was briefing the media on Friday. South Africa has recorded a total of 538,184 active cases. The majority of the new cases are from Gauteng and KwaZulu-Natal. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.